-- Hargreaves Lansdown Profit Rises 23% After Gaining New Clients
-- B y   H o w a r d   M u s t o e
-- 2012-09-05T07:00:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-05/hargreaves-lansdown-profit-rises-23-after-gaining-new-clients.html
Hargreaves Lansdown Plc (HL/) , the U.K.’s
largest retail broker, said full-year net income rose 23 percent
as it added new clients.  Profit for the year rose to 113 million pounds ($179
million) from 91.8 million pounds, the Bristol, England-based
company said in a statement today.  The firm now has 425,000 clients, an increase of 45,000
from last year, it said. Revenue grew 15 percent to 238.7
million pounds and assets under management rose 7 percent to
26.3 billion pounds.  “The group has continued to attract significant numbers of
new clients and is reporting increased profits despite a year
marked by economic and regulatory uncertainty,” Chairman
 Michael Evans  said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Howard Mustoe in London at 
